<dl id="n12189d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12189d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12189d"> 189(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ grantor</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> In most cases he does homage, or recognises in some other way the superiority of the <mark>grantor</mark>. There is always a right of reversion to the grantor, if the conditions on which the land was granted are not fulfilled. <small> W.F. Butler, &ldquo;Irish Land Tenures&rdquo; <a name="IRLT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IRLT"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (June 1924) 294</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
